#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an8.10"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an8.10:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 8 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.10:0.2"
msgid "1. Mettāvagga "
msgstr "1. Love "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an8.10:0.3"
msgid "10. Kāraṇḍavasutta "
msgstr "10. Trash "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an8.10:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā campāyaṃ viharati gaggarāya pokkharaṇiyā tīre. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Campā on the banks of the Gaggarā Lotus Pond. "

msgctxt "an8.10:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū bhikkhuṃ āpattiyā codenti. "
msgstr "Now at that time the mendicants accused a mendicant of an offense. "

msgctxt "an8.10:1.3"
msgid "So bhikkhu bhikkhūhi āpattiyā codiyamāno aññenāññaṃ paṭicarati, bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmeti, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti. "
msgstr "The accused mendicant dodged the issue, distracted the discussion with irrelevant points, and displayed annoyance, hate, and bitterness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.169, sc2
msgctxt "an8.10:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to the mendicants, "

msgctxt "an8.10:2.2"
msgid "“niddhamathetaṃ, bhikkhave, puggalaṃ; "
msgstr "“Mendicants, throw this person out! "

msgctxt "an8.10:2.3"
msgid "niddhamathetaṃ, bhikkhave, puggalaṃ. "
msgstr "Throw this person out! "

#. VAR: Apaneyyeso → apaneyyaso (bj) | apaneyyo (s1-3) | apaneyyo so (pts1)
msgctxt "an8.10:2.4"
msgid "Apaneyyeso, bhikkhave, puggalo. "
msgstr "This person should be shown the door. "

# NOTE: See BB’s note on the variants.
#. VAR: tena paraputtena visodhitena → kiṃ vo paraputto viheṭhiyati (bj) | kiṃ paraputto viheṭheti (s1-3) | kiṃ vo paraputtā viheṭheti (pts1) | kiṃ so paraputto visodheti (mr)
msgctxt "an8.10:2.5"
msgid "Kiṃ vo tena paraputtena visodhitena. "
msgstr "Why should you be vexed by an outsider? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.10:2.6"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa tādisaṃyeva hoti abhikkantaṃ paṭikkantaṃ ālokitaṃ vilokitaṃ samiñjitaṃ pasāritaṃ saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇaṃ, seyyathāpi aññesaṃ bhaddakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ—"
msgstr "Take a case where a certain person looks just the same as other good-natured mendicants when going out and coming back, when looking ahead and aside, when bending and extending the limbs, and when bearing the outer robe, bowl and robes. "

msgctxt "an8.10:2.7"
msgid "yāvassa bhikkhū āpattiṃ na passanti. "
msgstr "That is, so long as the mendicants don’t notice his offense. "

msgctxt "an8.10:2.8"
msgid "Yato ca khvassa bhikkhū āpattiṃ passanti, tamenaṃ evaṃ jānanti: "
msgstr "But when the mendicants notice the offense, they know that he’s "

#. VAR: samaṇadūsīvāyaṃ → samaṇarūpī cāyaṃ (mr)
#. VAR: samaṇakāraṇḍavo’ti → samaṇakaraṇḍavoti (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "an8.10:2.9"
msgid "‘samaṇadūsīvāyaṃ samaṇapalāpo samaṇakāraṇḍavo’ti. "
msgstr "a corrupt ascetic, just useless trash. "

msgctxt "an8.10:2.10"
msgid "Tamenaṃ iti viditvā bahiddhā nāsenti. "
msgstr "When they realize this they send him away. "

msgctxt "an8.10:2.11"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an8.10:2.12"
msgid "Mā aññe bhaddake bhikkhū dūsesīti. "
msgstr "So that he doesn’t corrupt good-natured mendicants. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.170, sc3
#. VAR: yavadūsī → yavarūpī (mr)
msgctxt "an8.10:3.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, sampanne yavakaraṇe yavadūsī jāyetha yavapalāpo yavakāraṇḍavoti. "
msgstr "Suppose in a growing field of barley some bad barley appeared, just useless trash. "

msgctxt "an8.10:3.2"
msgid "Tassa tādisaṃyeva mūlaṃ hoti, seyyathāpi aññesaṃ bhaddakānaṃ yavānaṃ; "
msgstr "Its roots, stem, and leaves would look just the same as the healthy barley. "

msgctxt "an8.10:3.3"
msgid "tādisaṃyeva nāḷaṃ hoti, seyyathāpi aññesaṃ bhaddakānaṃ yavānaṃ; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.10:3.4"
msgid "tādisaṃyeva pattaṃ hoti, seyyathāpi aññesaṃ bhaddakānaṃ yavānaṃ—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.10:3.5"
msgid "yāvassa sīsaṃ na nibbattati. "
msgstr "That is, so long as the head doesn’t appear. "

msgctxt "an8.10:3.6"
msgid "Yato ca khvassa sīsaṃ nibbattati, tamenaṃ evaṃ jānanti: "
msgstr "But when the head appears, they know that it’s "

msgctxt "an8.10:3.7"
msgid "‘yavadūsīvāyaṃ yavapalāpo yavakāraṇḍavo’ti. "
msgstr "bad barley, just useless trash. "

msgctxt "an8.10:3.8"
msgid "Tamenaṃ iti viditvā samūlaṃ uppāṭetvā bahiddhā yavakaraṇassa chaḍḍenti. "
msgstr "When they realize this they pull it up by the roots and throw it outside the field. "

msgctxt "an8.10:3.9"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an8.10:3.10"
msgid "Mā aññe bhaddake yave dūsesīti. "
msgstr "So that it doesn’t spoil the good barley. "

