#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
#. VAR: kuṭhāriṃ → kudhāriṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "an8.10:6.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso udapānapanāḷiyatthiko tiṇhaṃ kuṭhāriṃ ādāya vanaṃ paviseyya. "
msgstr "Suppose a man needs an irrigation gutter for a well. He’d take a sharp axe and enter the wood, "

# NOTE: Kakkhala here and daddara below are onomatapoeic. Kakkhala isn’t “dull” as BB has it, but ="crack, clap, click, clang, crackle “. Daddara ="thud, thump”
msgctxt "an8.10:6.2"
msgid "So yaṃ yadeva rukkhaṃ kuṭhāripāsena ākoṭeyya tattha yāni tāni rukkhāni daḷhāni sāravantāni tāni kuṭhāripāsena ākoṭitāni kakkhaḷaṃ paṭinadanti; "
msgstr "where he’d knock various trees with the axe. The trees that were firm and substantial made a cracking sound. "

msgctxt "an8.10:6.3"
msgid "yāni pana tāni rukkhāni antopūtīni avassutāni kasambujātāni tāni kuṭhāripāsena ākoṭitāni daddaraṃ paṭinadanti. "
msgstr "But the trees that were rotten inside, decomposing and decayed, made a thud. "

msgctxt "an8.10:6.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ mūle chindati, mūle chinditvā agge chindati, agge chinditvā anto suvisodhitaṃ visodheti, anto suvisodhitaṃ visodhetvā udapānapanāḷiṃ yojeti. "
msgstr "He’d cut down such a tree at the root, lop off the crown, and thoroughly clear out the insides. Then he’d use it as an irrigation gutter for the well. "

msgctxt "an8.10:6.5"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, idhekaccassa puggalassa tādisaṃyeva hoti abhikkantaṃ paṭikkantaṃ ālokitaṃ vilokitaṃ samiñjitaṃ pasāritaṃ saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇaṃ, seyyathāpi aññesaṃ bhaddakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ—"
